The Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) has invited the presidential candidate of the African Action Congress (AAC), Omoyele Sowore, and other Nigerian presidential candidates for the 2023 general elections to a youth political summit. The RCCG Directorate of Politics and Governance, Region 10, Abuja, and the FCT Pentecostal Fellowship of Nigeria (PFN) disclosed this in an invitation sent to the candidates and obtained by SaharaReporters On Friday. Other presidential candidates expected at the event included; Bola Tinubu of the All Progressives Congress (APC); Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP); Alhaji Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, the New Nigeria People’s Party (NNPP) and the Labour Party’s (LP) Peter Obi. They were all expected to speak on “Building a Nigeria with Youths as catalyst for Industrial Revolution.” The statement read, “The RCCG Directorate of Politics and Governance Region 10 Abuja in collaboration with the FCT Pentecostal Fellowship of Nigeria (PFN) invites the distinguished presence of ALL presidential candidates for the February 2023 general elections to the Abuja Youth Political Summit. “Theme: Building a Nigeria with Youths as catalyst for Industrial Revolution. Slated for; Date: 21st, January, 2023; Time: 1:00pm; Venue: RCCG, The Life Center. 27, I.B.M Haruna Crescent, Utako, Abuja. To discuss the future of the Nigerian Youth and her place in the next administration should ANY candidate be elected President and Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces, Federal Republic of Nigeria in the February 2023 general elections. “We hope to get a rapid response to our request and invitation. Be assured of our best regards.”